1
00:00:01,793 --> 00:00:03,253
[Lara, in English]
<i>Marcus, they're heading south.</i>

2
00:00:03,336 --> 00:00:04,337
<i>They're on the way to…</i>

3
00:00:04,421 --> 00:00:07,382
<i>to S. Trinidad Hospital.</i>

4
00:00:08,591 --> 00:00:10,635
[Jalil] <i>What's so special</i>
<i>about S. Trinidad Hospital?</i>

5
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:11,928
[Usman] <i>His mother is a surgeon</i>
<i>in that hospital.</i>

6
00:00:12,011 --> 00:00:14,222
[Jalil] <i>I'm coming for you, Jamilah.</i>

7
00:00:14,305 --> 00:00:15,140
<i>I'm coming to save you.</i>

8
00:00:15,223 --> 00:00:19,936
Operate on my brother,
and make sure he survives.

9
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:22,439
<i>If you don't want me to kill you all!</i>

10
00:00:22,522 --> 00:00:23,898
[Marcus, in English] <i>Listen up, everyone!</i>

11
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:25,942
[in English] <i>Our objective now,</i>
<i>secure the perimeter.</i>

12
00:00:26,025 --> 00:00:27,277
[Lara] <i>I've identified the patient.</i>

13
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:28,862
<i>His name is Tommy Rosales,</i>

14
00:00:28,945 --> 00:00:30,572
<i>the youngest brother</i>
<i>of Axl and Jovi Rosales.</i>

15
00:00:31,364 --> 00:00:34,284
<i>They're members</i>
<i>of the criminal group, Metal-13.</i>

16
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:36,202
[Marcus] <i>We can't be careless right now.</i>

17
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:37,746
[in English] We have
to negotiate with them.

18
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:39,414
[Marcus] <i>We will use the negotiation</i>

19
00:00:39,497 --> 00:00:41,750
<i>as a distraction before we attack them.</i>

20
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:42,459
- [monitor beeping rapidly]
- [Axl] <i>What's going on?!</i>

21
00:00:42,542 --> 00:00:44,419
What did you do to him?!

22
00:00:45,003 --> 00:00:47,630
[Axl] If you can't save our brother,

23
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:49,758
I'll shoot you straight in the head.

24
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:52,552
Agent Angeles, what's going on?

25
00:00:52,635 --> 00:00:55,221
[in English] Agent Reyes,
your negotiator just arrived.

26
00:00:55,305 --> 00:00:56,431
[Marcus] <i>Put him to work.</i>

27
00:00:56,514 --> 00:00:58,391
[suspenseful music playing]

28
00:00:58,475 --> 00:00:59,809
[Teresa] <i>Your brother is safe.</i>

29
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:02,812
[Teresa crying] <i>I've lost a child once.</i>

30
00:01:02,896 --> 00:01:07,275
<i>Sometimes, I wish I could've saved him</i>

31
00:01:07,358 --> 00:01:10,695
<i>the same way I save all of my patients.</i>

32
00:01:12,989 --> 00:01:15,950
[female reporter] <i>The hostage-taking</i>
<i>situation is still ongoing</i>

33
00:01:16,034 --> 00:01:17,952
<i>inside S. Trinidad Hospital.</i>

34
00:01:18,036 --> 00:01:22,248
<i>The group, Metal-13, is armed</i>
<i>with high-caliber weapons,</i>

35
00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:24,959
<i>keeping the police force in high alert</i>

36
00:01:25,043 --> 00:01:29,214
<i>for widespread gun smuggling operations</i>
<i>of syndicate groups.</i>

37
00:01:33,676 --> 00:01:39,516
[mysterious theme music playing]

38
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:51,486
- [monitor beeping steadily]
- [somber music playing]

39
00:01:57,075 --> 00:02:00,286
[grim music playing]

40
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:01,204
‪[music intensifies]

41
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:10,338
You're giving us
high-caliber weapons for free?

42
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:13,216
Is there a catch?

43
00:02:16,427 --> 00:02:18,304
[Felix] Of course, there is.

44
00:02:19,556 --> 00:02:22,100
You'll rob a bank, as you do,

45
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,269
with those weapons.

46
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:27,772
And however much you get from that,

47
00:02:28,356 --> 00:02:30,191
we'll divide it 60-40.

48
00:02:30,817 --> 00:02:33,528
Of course, the 60 is for me.

49
00:02:33,611 --> 00:02:36,739
[laughs]

50
00:02:38,199 --> 00:02:40,326
Wait, that's not fair.

51
00:02:41,327 --> 00:02:43,246
We're the ones doing the hard work,

52
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:45,373
and you'll get more than us?

53
00:02:45,456 --> 00:02:47,041
[Jovi] We can't allow that.

54
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:48,710
Let's do 50-50.

55
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:50,920
That's the deal.

56
00:02:51,504 --> 00:02:52,589
Alright!

57
00:02:53,715 --> 00:02:55,174
Let's do it 50-50!

58
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:56,593
Okay!

59
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:59,012
Like always.

60
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:03,141
If you fail,

61
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:04,726
I'll help you out.

62
00:03:05,768 --> 00:03:09,147
Just don't give me a hard time.

63
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:10,940
Okay?

64
00:03:11,649 --> 00:03:12,483
‪[music intensifies]

65
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:16,446
Do we have a deal?

66
00:03:17,155 --> 00:03:18,239
Huh?

67
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:25,788
[tense music playing]

68
00:03:35,089 --> 00:03:41,054
[music turns morose, concludes]

69
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:47,227
My gosh, sis.

70
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:50,897
Just when I've completed
my requirements for Canada,

71
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:52,815
I'm gonna die.

72
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:54,067
I can't take this.

73
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:57,153
That's what you get for teasing people.

74
00:03:57,237 --> 00:04:00,281
You got your karma,
but you dragged us along with you.

75
00:04:00,823 --> 00:04:02,075
- I'm sorry, sis.
- [somber music playing]

76
00:04:02,158 --> 00:04:02,992
‪[clicks tongue]

77
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:05,620
How about you, mister? How are you?

78
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:07,288
I'm alright.

79
00:04:08,039 --> 00:04:11,042
Hey! What are you doing? Stand up!

80
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:12,627
- [thug 1] Guard the doors!
- [thug 2 sighs]

81
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:15,004
Son of a…

82
00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:17,090
[Jovi] Axl.

83
00:04:17,715 --> 00:04:18,633
What's the plan?

84
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:23,763
‪[sniffles]

85
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:27,350
‪[gun thuds]

86
00:04:30,770 --> 00:04:32,772
[softly] We have to get out of here.

87
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:34,774
But how?

88
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:37,110
The TFA is waiting for us outside.

89
00:04:37,193 --> 00:04:39,195
They haven't moved.

90
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:40,863
I think

91
00:04:41,781 --> 00:04:43,074
they're going to negotiate first.

92
00:04:44,242 --> 00:04:46,995
[telephone ringing]

93
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:49,747
[tense music playing]

94
00:04:51,749 --> 00:04:52,875
[sniffles]

95
00:04:54,585 --> 00:04:57,088
[telephone ringing]

96
00:05:02,593 --> 00:05:03,636
Hello?

97
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,180
‪[suspenseful music playing]

98
00:05:06,264 --> 00:05:11,227
I am Director Emil Azuelo
of the Special Investigations Division.

99
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:16,065
May I talk with your leader?

100
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:19,152
Why? What do you need?

101
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:21,487
[Azuelo] <i>you're Axl Rosales, aren't you?</i>

102
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:26,409
I know that this isn't part of your plan.

103
00:05:27,243 --> 00:05:28,661
All you wanted

104
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:32,999
was to save your brother
who got shot, right?

105
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:37,003
<i>I'll let you get out of there alive,</i>

106
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:42,175
but only if you promise
not to hurt the hostages.

107
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:48,514
[suspenseful music playing]

108
00:05:49,098 --> 00:05:51,225
Do I make myself clear, Axl?

109
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:55,938
Did you really think
you can trick me that easily? Hmm?

110
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,654
I know what you're doing.

111
00:06:04,238 --> 00:06:06,741
You're trying to distract us
as you find your way in.

112
00:06:06,824 --> 00:06:08,034
[line rings]

113
00:06:09,368 --> 00:06:12,705
- Yes, Boss?
- Keep a close eye on the CCTVs.

114
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,791
Keep your eyes on the TFA.

115
00:06:14,874 --> 00:06:16,959
Yes, Boss. I'm on it.

116
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:24,050
[tense music playing]

117
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:31,641
Felix, you come with me.

118
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:33,226
We'll enter here.

119
00:06:37,313 --> 00:06:40,566
[Jalil] I'll enter
from the right with Sabdani.

120
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:45,571
[tense dramatic music continues]

121
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:31,075
Hey, you two.

122
00:07:32,493 --> 00:07:35,413
Keep an eye on the TFA outside.

123
00:07:35,496 --> 00:07:37,623
If they make a wrong move,

124
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:40,042
everyone in here will die!

125
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:42,962
[hostages screaming, crying in fear]

126
00:07:47,175 --> 00:07:52,263
[tense dramatic music continues]

127
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:47,109
[in English] Agent Reyes, armed hostile
approaching your corridor.

128
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:49,111
[in English] Maintain position.

129
00:08:51,572 --> 00:08:54,033
[in English] Marcus, clear to cross.

130
00:08:56,202 --> 00:09:02,041
[suspenseful music playing]

131
00:09:11,175 --> 00:09:12,677
Major Espina.

132
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,929
[Lara] <i>Slow down. There's</i>
<i>a movement to your right.</i>

133
00:09:26,065 --> 00:09:27,733
[grunts]

134
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:32,613
[both grunting]

135
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:45,835
[breathing heavily]

136
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:48,254
[in English] Espina, proceed.

137
00:09:52,717 --> 00:09:54,635
[in English] Monitor his vitals
every 15 minutes.

138
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:57,346
- Include the painkiller in his IV.
- Copy, Doc.

139
00:09:57,972 --> 00:10:02,059
Now, if you want the people in here
to come out alive…

140
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:07,023
give us our demands.

141
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:10,526
What do you need?

142
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:16,282
[in English] A helicopter.

143
00:10:18,826 --> 00:10:21,787
A big one. For all 13 of us.

144
00:10:22,496 --> 00:10:25,666
It's difficult to get a helicopter.

145
00:10:26,459 --> 00:10:29,253
It'll take a lot of time.

146
00:10:29,837 --> 00:10:31,213
If you want,

147
00:10:32,006 --> 00:10:33,924
I can give you a vehicle.

148
00:10:34,008 --> 00:10:36,177
You can go right now.

149
00:10:36,260 --> 00:10:37,762
How many do you need?

150
00:10:40,681 --> 00:10:43,726
What, so you can attack us
when we leave? Hmm?

151
00:10:43,809 --> 00:10:49,023
[suspenseful music playing]

152
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:53,736
I said… I want a helicopter.

153
00:10:54,362 --> 00:10:56,656
Can you give me that or not?

154
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:03,079
And I told you, it's difficult to get one.

155
00:11:03,162 --> 00:11:05,706
Can you wait three hours?

156
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:08,042
In three hours,

157
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:10,002
all of the people here would have died.

158
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:10,920
‪[dramatic sting]

159
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:15,883
- One hour?
- Thirty minutes.

160
00:11:19,136 --> 00:11:20,388
Alright.

161
00:11:21,055 --> 00:11:22,306
[in English] Thirty minutes.

162
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:29,355
- [suspenseful music continues]
- [sigh of relief]

163
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:46,205
Marcus.

164
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:49,291
[in English] Marcus, you have 30 minutes.

165
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:52,586
- [Lara, in English] <i>Thirty minutes.</i>
- [in English] Copy.

166
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:04,598
[tense music playing]

167
00:12:20,614 --> 00:12:22,241
[Azuelo] <i>Hello? Axl?</i>

168
00:12:22,783 --> 00:12:25,828
<i>I can't let you be the only ones happy.</i>

169
00:12:25,911 --> 00:12:30,332
I need to make sure
that you don't hurt the hostages.

170
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:32,877
What do you mean?

171
00:12:33,377 --> 00:12:35,254
You're asking for something.

172
00:12:36,005 --> 00:12:38,466
So, it's just fair that you give us
something in return.

173
00:12:45,639 --> 00:12:49,226
I want you to release ten hostages.

174
00:12:53,147 --> 00:12:55,858
And why would I do that? Hmm?

175
00:12:55,941 --> 00:12:58,152
Because you demanded something from us,

176
00:12:58,235 --> 00:13:01,530
so you have to give us something as well!

177
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:04,366
What if I just kill them all right now?

178
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:06,535
[people weeping]

179
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:11,290
[music intensifies]

180
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:18,964
Then, do it.

181
00:13:21,967 --> 00:13:24,553
But the moment we see blood,

182
00:13:25,429 --> 00:13:26,931
even just a drop,

183
00:13:27,515 --> 00:13:29,975
my men will rush in

184
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:31,560
and make sure you never get out.

185
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:36,565
[Azuelo] <i>But that's why</i>
<i>we're negotiating, right?</i>

186
00:13:37,316 --> 00:13:40,528
I'll let you get out of there alive,

187
00:13:40,611 --> 00:13:45,574
but make sure that no one gets hurt.

188
00:13:46,575 --> 00:13:50,704
[tense music continues]

189
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:56,460
Well?

190
00:13:57,586 --> 00:13:59,547
What do you say, Axl?

191
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:05,719
Alright.

192
00:14:06,554 --> 00:14:08,639
But make sure

193
00:14:08,722 --> 00:14:12,810
the helicopter arrives in 26 minutes.

194
00:14:13,310 --> 00:14:14,186
Otherwise…

195
00:14:15,563 --> 00:14:18,148
everyone in here will die.

196
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:31,245
[frustrated grunt]

197
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:38,127
[in English] Goddammit.

198
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:39,044
‪[music intensifies]

199
00:14:45,634 --> 00:14:46,677
[in English] Good job, sir.

200
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:51,515
[in English] Boys!

201
00:14:52,182 --> 00:14:55,477
Choose ten hostages to release.

202
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:58,772
[shouts] Now!

203
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:03,777
Only ten? It should be all of us!

204
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:06,238
Girl, shut up! I don't want to die yet!

205
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:07,740
- Don't say that!
- Stop it!

206
00:15:08,699 --> 00:15:11,035
- You! Come with me! Now!
- [woman sobs]

207
00:15:11,118 --> 00:15:12,786
You too!

208
00:15:12,870 --> 00:15:13,871
No!

209
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:16,457
Prioritize the patients! They matter more!

210
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:18,334
Whatever!

211
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:20,085
- [thug 1] Move!
- [hostages screaming]

212
00:15:20,169 --> 00:15:21,921
- [thug 1] Go!
- [screaming continues]

213
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:23,505
- [screams, sobs]
- [thug 1] Get out of here!

214
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:24,840
Hurry!

215
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:29,345
[clamoring, screaming]

216
00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:30,763
[thug 1] There!

217
00:15:30,846 --> 00:15:32,181
You too! Get up!

218
00:15:33,307 --> 00:15:34,391
[thug 1] Move!

219
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:36,685
- Come here!
- Hey!

220
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:39,438
Let me go! I can't leave!

221
00:15:39,521 --> 00:15:41,565
- Come on!
- Doc! Doc!

222
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:43,442
Go with him!

223
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:44,944
- I'll see you outside!
- [woman sobs]

224
00:15:45,027 --> 00:15:46,487
- Go!
- Cut that out!

225
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:47,404
Move!

226
00:15:47,488 --> 00:15:50,157
[tense music playing]

227
00:15:58,082 --> 00:15:59,750
[Jamilah] What are you doing?

228
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:01,418
- Doc!
- What are you doing?!

229
00:16:02,002 --> 00:16:03,212
- Put him in the wheelchair.
- [Teresa] Huh?

230
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:05,381
We can't! His wounds are still fresh!

231
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:06,674
I don't care!

232
00:16:06,757 --> 00:16:08,425
- [Jovi] Put him in the wheelchair!
- [woman] Let's go!

233
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:09,677
- Ken!
- [woman] Help!

234
00:16:10,302 --> 00:16:12,262
- [Teresa] Help us.
- Hurry.

235
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:15,599
- [Tommy groans in pain]
- Be careful.

236
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:17,977
- One.
- [Tommy groans]

237
00:16:19,311 --> 00:16:21,522
- [Jovi] Be careful!
- [Tommy grunts]

238
00:16:27,236 --> 00:16:32,992
[intriguing music playing]

239
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:37,496
What the hell do you think you're doing?

240
00:16:37,579 --> 00:16:38,914
Go help them!

241
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:41,208
Move!

242
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:46,046
[suspenseful music playing]

243
00:16:47,631 --> 00:16:49,299
[in English] Domingo, next left.

244
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:51,927
- The third one's the control room.
- [radio static]

245
00:16:55,472 --> 00:16:57,766
- [in English] Copy, madam.
- [static crackles]

246
00:16:59,768 --> 00:17:04,565
[sirens wailing]

247
00:17:06,817 --> 00:17:08,027
[tires screech]

248
00:17:11,947 --> 00:17:13,365
POLICE

249
00:17:15,784 --> 00:17:21,040
[suspenseful music playing]

250
00:17:28,213 --> 00:17:29,465
Sir, where are you going?

251
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:30,966
My niece is inside.

252
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:32,509
It's not safe to go inside.

253
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:33,886
Please move back.

254
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:38,098
Omar, what if Jamilah's in danger?

255
00:17:38,807 --> 00:17:40,142
We're barging in there.

256
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:41,810
We'll save Jamilah.

257
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:47,274
[music intensifies]

258
00:17:53,322 --> 00:17:54,364
[thug] Keep moving!

259
00:17:56,575 --> 00:17:57,826
Go!

260
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:01,497
[suspenseful music continues]

261
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:02,790
Be quiet!

262
00:18:15,844 --> 00:18:18,013
[in English] Agent Castillo,
hostile approaching your way.

263
00:18:18,889 --> 00:18:19,932
I'll take care of it.

264
00:18:20,015 --> 00:18:21,850
- Move forward.
- Are you sure?

265
00:18:21,934 --> 00:18:23,352
I got this.

266
00:18:27,314 --> 00:18:28,398
[in English] Yes, sir.

267
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:34,279
[suspenseful music continues]

268
00:18:36,156 --> 00:18:38,784
[both grunt]

269
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:40,035
[Castillo grunts]

270
00:18:41,620 --> 00:18:42,579
[assailant grunts]

271
00:18:52,172 --> 00:18:57,469
[suspenseful music continues]

272
00:18:57,553 --> 00:18:58,971
Weapons down!

273
00:18:59,555 --> 00:19:00,472
[thug 2] Down!

274
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:02,474
[thug 2] Put 'em down!

275
00:19:03,183 --> 00:19:04,852
We come in peace.

276
00:19:05,686 --> 00:19:07,396
We're here for the hostages.

277
00:19:08,397 --> 00:19:13,902
[suspenseful music continues]

278
00:19:37,551 --> 00:19:38,719
[policeman 1] Go! Double-time!

279
00:19:38,802 --> 00:19:40,095
[policeman 2] Move!

280
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:45,934
- [hostages screaming]
- Come on! This way!

281
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:54,151
[suspenseful music continues]

282
00:19:54,234 --> 00:19:55,194
[assailant grunts]

283
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:11,501
- [hostages sobbing]
- [woman] Don't hurt us!

284
00:20:34,149 --> 00:20:37,236
[suspenseful music continues]

285
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:40,656
[in English] Espina, stand by
for rendezvous with Agent Reyes.

286
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:42,074
Be alert.

287
00:20:42,157 --> 00:20:44,284
- There's a guard outside the ER.
- [radio static]

288
00:20:49,289 --> 00:20:53,001
[music turns tense]

289
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:04,596
[in English] In position.

290
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,556
- [in English] I'm in position.
- [static crackles]

291
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:17,442
[keyboard clacking]

292
00:21:30,539 --> 00:21:32,833
[breathing heavily]

293
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:36,753
[phone ringing]

294
00:21:37,671 --> 00:21:38,672
- Hello?
- [Guard] <i>Boss!</i>

295
00:21:38,755 --> 00:21:41,675
The cameras are on a loop!
They hacked the CCTV system!

296
00:21:41,758 --> 00:21:43,093
They must be inside already!

297
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:45,971
- [rapid gunfire]
- [guard grunts]

298
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:49,891
They tricked us.

299
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:54,980
[body thuds]

300
00:21:55,063 --> 00:21:59,860
[unsettling music playing]

301
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:11,830
[suspenseful music playing]

302
00:22:11,913 --> 00:22:16,460
[tense music playing]

303
00:22:16,543 --> 00:22:17,836
You bastards!

304
00:22:17,919 --> 00:22:19,838
<i>I'm going to kill everyone!</i>

305
00:22:19,921 --> 00:22:22,090
Everyone!

306
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:23,133
[yells]

307
00:22:24,092 --> 00:22:26,887
[tense music playing]

308
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:41,276
[screams]

309
00:22:59,711 --> 00:23:05,926
[music intensifies]

310
00:23:19,022 --> 00:23:24,903
[tense music continues]

311
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:35,080
I'll take care of him. Get out of here!

312
00:23:35,163 --> 00:23:36,832
- Where are you taking her?!
- Jamilah!

313
00:23:36,915 --> 00:23:37,666
[Axl] <i>Go!</i>

314
00:23:37,749 --> 00:23:39,876
[Jalil] <i>We need to split up.</i>

315
00:23:41,545 --> 00:23:42,420
Lara, where are they?

316
00:23:42,504 --> 00:23:44,297
Agent Reyes, they're heading
to the north wing.

317
00:23:44,381 --> 00:23:45,423
Hey!

318
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:52,389
[Norhana] <i>Allah! Allah,</i>
<i>please keep Jamilah safe. Allah!</i>

319
00:23:52,472 --> 00:23:54,933
They have another hostage. A Muslim girl.

320
00:23:55,016 --> 00:23:55,976
Jamilah.

321
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:58,937
- [gunshots]
- [grunts]

322
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:03,525
Dr. Teresa and I already
treated your brother.

323
00:24:03,608 --> 00:24:05,485
- [Teresa] <i>Just surrender.</i>
- Get up!

324
00:24:06,695 --> 00:24:08,280
[Jovi] <i>Protect yourself.</i>

325
00:24:09,698 --> 00:24:10,949
[Marcus] <i>Face me.</i>

326
00:24:11,032 --> 00:24:13,618
[both grunting]

327
00:24:13,702 --> 00:24:14,619
[Jalil] <i>Freeze!</i>

328
00:24:15,871 --> 00:24:18,039
- [Jalil] <i>Don't hurt her!</i>
- [Axl] <i>I'm going to kill her!</i>

329
00:24:19,666 --> 00:24:21,418
- [blow lands]
- [groans]
